{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KcyXC4WtuK7qFdiTxY3GzC","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 2.4: Init Command — Workflow Generation\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a developer,\n10\tI want `codeharness init` to generate a default workflow in my project,\n11\tso that I can start using codeharness without manual setup.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** a project without `.codeharness/workflows/`\n16\t   **When** `codeharness init` runs\n17\t   **Then** `.codeharness/workflows/default.yaml` is created with contents identical to the embedded template at `templates/workflows/default.yaml`\n18\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n19\t\n20\t2. **Given** a project that already has `.codeharness/workflows/default.yaml`\n21\t   **When** `codeharness init` runs without `--force`\n22\t   **Then** the existing workflow file is NOT overwritten and an info message is logged indicating the file already exists\n23\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t3. **Given** a project that already has `.codeharness/workflows/default.yaml`\n26\t   **When** `codeharness init --force` runs\n27\t   **Then** the existing workflow file IS overwritten with the latest embedded template\n28\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n29\t\n30\t4. **Given** the `--force` flag is added to the init command\n31\t   **When** `codeharness init --help` is inspected\n32\t   **Then** the `--force` option appears in the help output with description indicating it overwrites existing generated files\n33\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n34\t\n35\t5. **Given** `codeharness init` runs successfully with workflow generation\n36\t   **When** the console output is inspected\n37\t   **Then** a success message `[OK] Workflow: .codeharness/workflows/default.yaml created` appears in the output (or `[INFO] Workflow: .codeharness/workflows/default.yaml already exists` if skipped)\n38\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n39\t\n40\t6. **Given** the existing stack detection functionality in `initProject()`\n41\t   **When** `codeharness init` runs after this change\n42\t   **Then** stack detection still works identically — no regressions in detected stack, app type, or stacks array\n43\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n44\t\n45\t7. **Given** the init command runs with `--json` flag\n46\t   **When** workflow generation completes\n47\t   **Then** the JSON output includes a `workflow` field with `{ status: 'created' | 'exists' | 'overwritten', path: '.codeharness/workflows/default.yaml' }`\n48\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n49\t\n50\t8. **Given** unit tests for workflow generation during init\n51\t   **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n52\t   **Then** tests pass covering: new project gets workflow copied, existing workflow is preserved without `--force`, existing workflow is overwritten with `--force`, `--json` output includes workflow field, and no regressions in existing init tests\n53\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n54\t\n55\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n56\t\n57\t- [x] Task 1: Add `--force` flag to init command registration (AC: #3, #4)\n58\t  - [x] Add `--force` option to `registerInitCommand()` in `src/commands/init.ts`\n59\t  - [x] Pass `force` through `InitOptions` type in `src/modules/infra/types.ts`\n60\t\n61\t- [x] Task 2: Implement workflow generation step in `initProjectInner()` (AC: #1, #2, #3, #5, #7)\n62\t  - [x] Add workflow generation step after stack detection but before Docker check\n63\t  - [x] Use `getPackageRoot()` from `src/lib/templates.ts` to locate `templates/workflows/default.yaml`\n64\t  - [x] Use `fs.copyFileSync` to copy the embedded template to `.codeharness/workflows/default.yaml`\n65\t  - [x] Create `.codeharness/workflows/` directory with `mkdirSync({ recursive: true })`\n66\t  - [x] Skip copy if target exists and `--force` is not set; log info message\n67\t  - [x] Overwrite if target exists and `--force` is set; log overwrite message\n68\t  - [x] Add `workflow` field to `InitResult` type\n69\t\n70\t- [x] Task 3: Update `handleRerun()` for idempotent workflow check (AC: #2, #6)\n71\t  - [x] On re-run, skip workflow generation (already handled by exists check)\n72\t  - [x] Verify re-run path does not regress\n73\t\n74\t- [x] Task 4: Write unit tests (AC: #8)\n75\t  - [x] Test: new project gets `.codeharness/workflows/default.yaml` created\n76\t  - [x] Test: existing workflow file is preserved without `--force`\n77\t  - [x] Test: existing workflow file is overwritten with `--force`\n78\t  - [x] Test: `--json` output includes `workflow` field\n79\t  - [x] Test: no regressions — existing init-project tests still pass\n80\t\n81\t## Dev Notes\n82\t\n83\t### Module Location and Architecture Role\n84\t\n85\tThis story modifies the existing init command flow. The changes touch:\n86\t- `src/commands/init.ts` — add `--force` option registration\n87\t- `src/modules/infra/types.ts` — add `force` to `InitOptions`, add `workflow` to `InitResult`\n88\t- `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts` — add workflow generation step to `initProjectInner()`\n89\t\n90\tThe init command is a thin wrapper (`68 lines`) that delegates to `initProject()` in `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts`. All business logic goes into `init-project.ts`, not the command file.\n91\t\n92\t### Workflow File Copy Pattern\n93\t\n94\tThe architecture (AD3) states: \"The `codeharness init` command copies the default workflow to the project.\" This is a simple file copy, not a template render — the default workflow YAML has no `{{VAR}}` placeholders.\n95\t\n96\tUse `getPackageRoot()` from `src/lib/templates.ts` to locate the embedded template:\n97\t```typescript\n98\timport { getPackageRoot } from '../../lib/templates.js';\n99\tconst src = join(getPackageRoot(), 'templates/workflows/default.yaml');\n100\tconst dest = join(projectDir, '.codeharness/workflows/default.yaml');\n101\t```\n102\t\n103\tUse `fs.existsSync()` + `fs.copyFileSync()` — no need for `renderTemplateFile()` since there are no template variables. Use `mkdirSync(dirname(dest), { recursive: true })` to ensure the directory exists.\n104\t\n105\t### Output Conventions (Established by `init-project.ts`)\n106\t\n107\tThe init command uses these output helpers from `src/lib/output.ts`:\n108\t- `okOutput(msg)` — green `[OK] msg`\n109\t- `info(msg)` — blue `[INFO] msg`\n110\t- `warn(msg)` — yellow `[WARN] msg`\n111\t- `failOutput(msg)` — red `[FAIL] msg`\n112\t\n113\tFollow the same pattern:\n114\t- Created: `okOutput('Workflow: .codeharness/workflows/default.yaml created')`\n115\t- Exists: `info('Workflow: .codeharness/workflows/default.yaml already exists')`\n116\t- Overwritten: `okOutput('Workflow: .codeharness/workflows/default.yaml overwritten')`\n117\t\n118\t### `--force` Flag Scope\n119\t\n120\tThe `--force` flag in this story only affects workflow file generation. Future stories may expand its scope (e.g., agent configs in story 3.2). Keep the logic modular so `force` can be checked independently per generation step.\n121\t\n122\t### Insertion Point in `initProjectInner()`\n123\t\n124\tAdd the workflow generation step after stack detection (line ~91 in current code) and before Docker check (line ~101). This keeps workflow generation early and independent of Docker/observability configuration. The step should:\n125\t1. Compute source and destination paths\n126\t2. Check if destination exists\n127\t3. Copy or skip based on `force` flag\n128\t4. Update `result.workflow` object\n129\t5. Emit appropriate console output\n130\t\n131\t### JSON Output Extension\n132\t\n133\tThe `InitResult` type (in `src/modules/infra/types.ts`) needs a new optional `workflow` field:\n134\t```typescript\n135\tworkflow?: { status: 'created' | 'exists' | 'overwritten'; path: string };\n136\t```\n137\t\n138\t### Anti-Patterns to Avoid\n139\t\n140\t- **Do NOT use `renderTemplateFile()`** for this copy — the default workflow has no placeholders\n141\t- **Do NOT read the YAML and re-serialize** — use `copyFileSync` to preserve exact formatting\n142\t- **Do NOT put business logic in `src/commands/init.ts`** — it stays a thin wrapper\n143\t- **Do NOT modify `templates/workflows/default.yaml`** — it was created in story 2.3 and is correct\n144\t- **Do NOT change `package.json` files array** — `templates/workflows/` was already added in story 2.3\n145\t\n146\t### Existing Test Patterns\n147\t\n148\tInit tests are heavily mocked. See `src/modules/infra/__tests__/init-project.test.ts` for the pattern:\n149\t- Mock `fs` functions (`existsSync`, `readFileSync`, `writeFileSync`, etc.)\n150\t- Mock `stack-detect`, `deps-install`, `docker-setup`, `bmad-setup`\n151\t- Assert on `Result<InitResult>` shape\n152\t- For workflow generation tests: mock `existsSync` for the destination path, assert `copyFileSync` or `writeFileSync` was called with correct args\n153\t\n154\t### What This Story Does NOT Do\n155\t\n156\t- **Does not create the validate command** (story 2.5)\n157\t- **Does not create agent YAML files** (story 3.2)\n158\t- **Does not implement workflow patching** (story 9.1)\n159\t- **Does not change the existing default workflow YAML** — that's story 2.3's output\n160\t- **Does not add `--force` to any other files** (e.g., agents) — that's future stories\n161\t\n162\t### Project Structure Notes\n163\t\n164\t- Modified file: `src/commands/init.ts` — add `--force` option\n165\t- Modified file: `src/modules/infra/types.ts` — extend `InitOptions` and `InitResult`\n166\t- Modified file: `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts` — add workflow generation step\n167\t- Modified file: `src/modules/infra/__tests__/init-project.test.ts` — add workflow generation tests\n168\t- No new files created (all changes are additions to existing files)\n169\t\n170\t### References\n171\t\n172\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-v2.md#Story 2.4: Init Command — Workflow Generation]\n173\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD3: Embedded Template Storage]\n174\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#Project Structure — src/commands/init.ts]\n175\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/2-3-default-embedded-workflow.md — templates/workflows/default.yaml location, parseWorkflow API]\n176\t- [Source: src/modules/infra/init-project.ts — initProjectInner flow, output conventions, result shape]\n177\t- [Source: src/lib/templates.ts — getPackageRoot() for locating embedded templates]\n178\t\n179\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n180\t## Verification Requirements\n181\t\n182\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/2-4-init-command-workflow-generation-proof.md)\n183\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n184\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (80%)\n185\t\n186\t## Documentation Requirements\n187\t\n188\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n189\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/2-4-init-command-workflow-generation.md\n190\t\n191\t## Testing Requirements\n192\t\n193\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n194\t- [ ] Coverage target: 80%\n195\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n196\t\n197\t## Dev Agent Record\n198\t\n199\t### Agent Model Used\n200\t\n201\tClaude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n202\t\n203\t### Debug Log References\n204\t\n205\t### Completion Notes List\n206\t\n207\t- Task 1: Added `--force` flag to `registerInitCommand()` with default `false`. Added `force` to `CommandInitOptions` and `InitOptions`. Passed through to `initProject()`.\n208\t- Task 2: Added workflow generation step in `initProjectInner()` after stack detection, before Dockerfile template generation. Uses `getPackageRoot()` + `copyFileSync`. Creates directory with `mkdirSync({ recursive: true })`. Handles create/exists/overwrite states with correct output messages. Added `workflow` field to `InitResult`.\n209\t- Task 3: Updated `handleRerun()` to populate `result.workflow` with `exists` status when workflow file is already present.\n210\t- Task 4: Added 5 unit tests covering: fresh creation, preservation without `--force`, overwrite with `--force`, JSON output inclusion, and stack detection non-regression. All 30 tests pass (25 original + 5 new). Full suite: 3614 tests pass, 0 regressions.\n211\t\n212\t### Change Log\n213\t\n214\t- 2026-04-02: Implemented story 2-4 — init command workflow generation with `--force` flag support\n215\t- 2026-04-02: Code review — fixed handleRerun() to respect --force flag and handle missing workflow on re-run; added 3 re-run tests\n216\t\n217\t### File List\n218\t\n219\t- src/commands/init.ts (modified — added `--force` option and `force` field)\n220\t- src/modules/infra/types.ts (modified — added `force` to `InitOptions`, `workflow` to `InitResult`)\n221\t- src/modules/infra/init-project.ts (modified — added workflow generation step, updated imports, updated `handleRerun()`, fixed re-run --force handling)\n222\t- src/modules/infra/__tests__/init-project.test.ts (modified — added 5 workflow generation tests + 3 re-run workflow tests)\n223\t\n224\t### Senior Developer Review (AI)\n225\t\n226\t**Reviewer:** Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n227\t**Date:** 2026-04-02\n228\t**Outcome:** Changes Requested -> Fixed\n229\t\n230\t**Issues Found: 2 HIGH, 1 MEDIUM, 2 LOW**\n231\t\n232\t| # | Severity | Description | Status |\n233\t|---|----------|-------------|--------|\n234\t| 1 | MEDIUM | `handleRerun()` ignored `--force` flag — workflow never overwritten on re-run | FIXED |\n235\t| 2 | MEDIUM | `handleRerun()` left `result.workflow` undefined when file missing on re-run | FIXED |\n236\t| 3 | MEDIUM | No test coverage for re-run + `--force` workflow overwrite path | FIXED (3 tests added) |\n237\t| 4 | LOW | No descriptive error when template source file missing (falls to generic catch) | Noted |\n238\t| 5 | LOW | Relative path `.codeharness/workflows/default.yaml` repeated 7+ times without constant | Noted |\n239\t\n240\t**Fixes Applied:**\n241\t- `init-project.ts` `handleRerun()`: Added full workflow generation logic with `--force` support and missing-file recovery\n242\t- `init-project.test.ts`: Added 3 new tests — re-run+force overwrite, re-run missing file creation, re-run preserve without force\n243\t\n244\t**Coverage:** 96.64% overall, all 150 files above 80% per-file floor. 33 init-project tests passing.\n245\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_018s9cvCvVdbUHD19Co6cJtQ","session_id":"5fca15c0-771e-463c-9e4f-c528b230e359","uuid":"45899b2d-4df2-440f-bcc9-d95eaf3bd76e","timestamp":"2026-04-02T14:48:14.344Z"}
