{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_011LfAna188LEspXeyxGX9qj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0112QNZj17LBTML9ifR7oQVB","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/2-5-validate-command.md","old_string":"- [ ] Task 1: Decide command structure — subcommands vs replacement (AC: #6)\n  - [ ] Evaluate whether to add `validate schema` subcommand or restructure `validate` with `validate self` / `validate schema`\n  - [ ] The existing `validate` command (self-validation) has no known external consumers calling it programmatically, so either approach works. Document decision in dev notes.\n\n- [ ] Task 2: Implement the schema validation command handler (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4, #5, #7)\n  - [ ] Create a new command registration function (e.g., `registerValidateSchemaCommand`) or modify existing `registerValidateCommand`\n  - [ ] Discover `.codeharness/workflows/*.yaml` files in the project directory\n  - [ ] For each discovered YAML file, call `parseWorkflow(filePath)` and catch `WorkflowParseError`\n  - [ ] Map `WorkflowParseError.errors` to user-facing output with file path, violation path, and message\n  - [ ] Handle missing directory gracefully (no crash)\n  - [ ] Set `process.exitCode = 0` if all files valid, `process.exitCode = 1` if any invalid\n\n- [ ] Task 3: Implement JSON output mode (AC: #5)\n  - [ ] When `--json` is set, output `{ status: 'pass' | 'fail', files: [{ path, valid, errors }] }`\n  - [ ] Use `jsonOutput()` from `src/lib/output.ts`\n\n- [ ] Task 4: Restructure existing validate command if needed (AC: #6)\n  - [ ] If subcommand approach chosen: register as `validate schema` and rename existing to `validate self`\n  - [ ] If replacement approach: move self-validation to `validate self`, make `validate` default to schema validation\n  - [ ] Update `src/index.ts` command registration\n\n- [ ] Tas