t for non-`WorkflowParseError` exception path in `runSchemaValidation` (FIXED)\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- `process.chdir()` in `validate-schema.test.ts` mutates global state; could use `vi.spyOn(process, 'cwd')` instead for isolation\n- `process.cwd()` hardcoded in both command actions — no `--dir` option for programmatic use from different working directories\n- `validate.ts` imports `runSchemaValidation` separately from `renderSchemaResult` — could simplify to a single `runAndRenderSchemaValidation()` but current approach is fine for testability\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- `validate-self.ts` lines 46 and 86: uncovered branches in error reporting JSON path and outputHuman failure loop — pre-existing from story 10-3\n- No integration test that exercises the full CLI binary (only commander `parseAsync` in-process tests)\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None significant. The thin-wrapper pattern is followed correctly. `runSchemaValidation` is a pure function taking `projectDir`, `renderSchemaResult` handles output — clean separation.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 21\n- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 12, Edit: 6, Grep: 0, Write: 0, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npm test | grep` (~170 lines), `codeharness coverage` (~5 lines), `npm run test:unit` (~10 lines)\n- Files read: 11 unique, 13 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: 1 re-read of `validate-schema.test.ts` (offset read after full read — justified to see end of file); 1 re-read of `validate-schema.ts` was cached by tool"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ad2e331ad8f861244 (use SendMessage with to: 'ad2e331ad8f861244' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 62659\ntool_uses: 40\nduration_ms: 366940</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5fca15c0-771e-463c-9e4f-c528b230e359","uuid":"b5b094f9-91de-4447-80b7-f628fdad0535","ti