{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015T8EgBZBVV9WinWcLPGcYw","type":"tool_result","content":"600\t---\n601\t\n602\t## 3. Cost Analysis\n603\t\n604\t### Session Cost\n605\t\n606\t`codeharness stats --save` failed — session-logs directory still missing (deleted in story 1-2, not yet rebuilt). Cost data is reconstructed from subagent token reports in `.session-issues.md`.\n607\t\n608\t**Aggregate Tool Usage Across All 4 Phases (Story 2-2):**\n609\t\n610\t| Tool | create-story | dev-story | code-review | verification | Total |\n611\t|------|-------------|-----------|-------------|--------------|-------|\n612\t| Bash | 3 | 6 | 7 | 13 | **29** |\n613\t| Read | 8 | 5 | 5 | 3 | **21** |\n614\t| Edit | 0 | 3 | 3 | 1 | **7** |\n615\t| Write | 1 | 2 | 0 | 1 | **4** |\n616\t| Grep | 2 | 0 | 1 | 5 | **8** |\n617\t| Glob | 5 | 0 | 0 | 0 | **5** |\n618\t| Skill | 0 | 0 | 1 | 0 | **1** |\n619\t| **Total** | **16** | **13** | **15** | **19** | **63** |\n620\t\n621\t**Files Read:** ~25 unique files across session.\n622\t\n623\t### Subagent-Level Breakdown\n624\t\n625\t**Phase 1 — create-story (16 calls):** Clean execution. 8 Read calls to gather context, 5 Glob to locate files. Zero redundant operations. Smallest Bash outputs (~12 lines max). Efficient.\n626\t\n627\t**Phase 2 — dev-story (13 calls):** Leanest dev phase of the day. 6 Bash (test runs, coverage), 5 Read, 3 Edit, 2 Write. Coverage command used appropriately. No redundancy reported.\n628\t\n629\t**Phase 3 — code-review (15 calls):** Found and fixed 2 MEDIUM issues. 7 Bash (coverage run, test runs), 5 Read, 3 Edit. One extra coverage grep needed — minor redundancy. Cost justified by real bugs found.\n630\t\n631\t**Phase 4 — verification (19 calls):** Most call-heavy phase. 13 Bash calls includes `npm test` (~80 lines output) and `npx vitest --coverage` (~80 lines output). Coverage was run twice (first grep didn't show workflow-parser). Still the most expensive phase proportionally.\n632\t\n633\t### Efficiency Comparison Across Sessions\n634\t\n635\t| Session | Story | Total Tool Calls | Calls/Phase | Type |\n636\t|---------|-------|-----------------|-------------|------|\n637\t| 1 | 1-1 + 1-2 | ~233 | ~29 | Deletion |\n638\t| 2 | 1-3 | 74 | 18.5 | Greenfield |\n639\t| 3 | 2-1 | ~86 | ~21.5 | Greenfield |\n640\t| 4 | 2-2 | 63 | 15.75 | Greenfield |\n641\t\n642\t**Story 2-2 was the most efficient story of the day at 15.75 calls/phase.** This is a 46% improvement over Session 1's deletion stories and a 15% improvement over the previous best (Session 2).\n643\t\n644\t### Token Waste Hotspots (Story 2-2)\n645\t\n646\t1. **Coverage run twice in verification** — first grep didn't match. Could be avoided with `--no-color` and direct output capture.\n647\t2. **`npm test` output at ~80 lines** — could be trimmed with `--silent` flag.\n648\t3. **No other significant waste reported.** This was the cleanest session of the day.\n649\t\n650\t### Estimated Session Cost\n651\t\n652\tBased on the cost-per-call rate from Session 3 ($15.37 / 119 calls = ~$0.13/call), Session 4's 63 calls estimates to **~$8.19**. This is conservative — greenfield stories tend to have smaller context windows.\n653\t\n654\t### Full-Day Cost Summary\n655\t\n656\t| Session | Story(ies) | Tool Calls | Estimated Cost |\n657\t|---------|-----------|-----------|----------------|\n658\t| 1 | 1-1, 1-2 | ~233 | ~$10 (estimated) |\n659\t| 2 | 1-3 | 74 | ~$5.48 (from stats) |\n660\t| 3 | 2-1 | ~86 | ~$8.34 (from stats) |\n661\t| 4 | 2-2 | 63 | ~$8.19 (estimated) |\n662\t| Orchestrator overhead | — | ~15 | ~$3-4 |\n663\t| **Full Day Total** | **5 stories** | **~471** | **~$35** |\n664\t\n665\t### Cumulative Sprint Cost\n666\t\n667\t- Historical cumulative: $900.92 (158 stories prior)\n668\t- Today: ~$35\n669\t- **Running total: ~$936**\n670\t- **Average cost per story today: ~$7/story** (vs historical $4.17/story)\n671\t\n672\tThe higher per-story cost today reflects Opus 4 pricing (cache reads at $1.50/MTok) and larger context windows from accumulated v2 architecture artifacts. The absolute numbers are still well within budget.\n673\t\n674\t---\n675\t\n676\t## 4. What Went Well\n677\t\n678\t1. **Most efficient session of the day.** 63 tool calls, 15.75 calls/phase — steady improvement across all 4 sessions.\n679\t2. **Zero redundant operations in create-story and dev-story.** The cleanest subagent execution logged today.\n680\t3. **Code review caught real error-handling bugs.** The `readFileSync` catch-all masking permission errors and directory-as-path errors would have been confusing failures in production.\n681\t4. **Defaults handling correctly identified and implemented.** The observation that ajv does NOT apply defaults (from create-story) was correctly propagated to dev-story implementation.\n682\t5. **Overall test coverage held at 96.63%** with all 150 files above 80% floor. 20 tests for the parser module.\n683\t6. **Five stories completed in a single day.** Epic 1 fully done, Epic 2 at 40% (2/5). Strong velocity.\n684\t\n685\t---\n686\t\n687\t## 5. What Went Wrong\n688\t\n689\t1. **`codeharness stats` still broken.** Fourth session with no fix. Session-logs directory deleted in story 1-2, never rebuilt. All cost data is manual reconstruction from token reports.\n690\t2. **Pre-existing test failures persist.** 6 query metrics tests and 4 BATS integration tests failing since story 1-2. These are not blocking but accumulate as noise in every test run.\n691\t3. **Verification format sensitivity recurred.** `**Tier:** test-provable` must be in bold markdown — same format issue in all 4 sessions. Still not fixed in subagent instructions.\n692\t4. **Branch coverage gaps deferred again.** `String(err)` fallback, EACCES path, ajv internals — each individually LOW but collectively they represent ~10 uncovered branches across stories 2-1 and 2-2.\n693\t5. **`_bmad/config.yaml` location confusion recurred.** Fourth time the create-story agent had to resolve this via glob. Should be documented or fixed.\n694\t\n695\t---\n696\t\n697\t## 6. Lessons Learned\n698\t\n699\t### Patterns to Repeat\n700\t\n701\t- **Greenfield modules get more efficient over time.** Each successive greenfield story was leaner: 74 -> 86 -> 63 tool calls. The pattern is maturing.\n702\t- **Explicit defaults observation in create-story.** Noting that ajv does NOT apply defaults prevented a potential bug where the parser would return incomplete workflow objects.\n703\t- **Lean dev-story phases.** 13 calls for story 2-2 dev is close to the theoretical minimum for a new module with tests. The dev-story skill has learned the codebase patterns.\n704\t- **Code review as error-handling auditor.** Both MEDIUM findings were error-handling issues — catch-all masking real errors. This is a pattern code review consistently catches.\n705\t\n706\t### Patterns to Avoid\n707\t\n708\t- **Not fixing the stats command.** Four sessions of manual cost reconstruction. The ROI on fixing this is obvious.\n709\t- **Not fixing pre-existing test failures.** Six failing tests create noise and slow down verification (false negatives to investigate).\n710\t- **Not documenting `_bmad/config.yaml` location.** Four sessions, same confusion. Add it to project context or create the expected path as a symlink.\n711\t\n712\t---\n713\t\n714\t## 7. Action Items\n715\t\n716\t| # | Action | Priority | Status |\n717\t|---|--------|----------|--------|\n718\t| 1 | **FIX: Add proof format specification to verification skill prompt** | CRITICAL | Carried x3 — STILL NOT DONE |\n719\t| 2 | **FIX: `codeharness stats` to handle missing session-logs directory** | HIGH | Carried x3 |\n720\t| 3 | Fix `package.json` `files` array — remove stale `ralph/**/*.sh` and `ralph/AGENTS.md` | HIGH | Carried x3 |\n721\t| 4 | Fix pre-existing query metrics test failures (6 tests) | MEDIUM | New |\n722\t| 5 | Remove or fix BATS integration tests referencing deleted shell scripts | MEDIUM | New |\n723\t| 6 | Add `--no-color` to vitest invocations in subagent prompts | MEDIUM | Carried x2 |\n724\t| 7 | Document `_bmad/config.yaml` location in project context | LOW | New |\n725\t| 8 | Begin story 2-3-default-embedded-workflow | HIGH | Next session |\n726\t\n727\t---\n728\t\n729\t## Full-Day Final Summary (2026-04-02)\n730\t\n731\t### Stories Completed\n732\t\n733\t| # | Story | Epic | Type | Tool Calls | Key Review Findings |\n734\t|---|-------|------|------|-----------|-------------------|\n735\t| 1 | 1-1-delete-beads-integration | 1 | Deletion | ~119 | Dead type members, stale JSDoc |\n736\t| 2 | 1-2-delete-ralph-loop-legacy-verification | 1 | Deletion | ~114 | Incomplete ralph/ deletion, broken stats.ts |\n737\t| 3 | 1-3-workflow-state-module | 1 | Greenfield | 74 | Naming collision, validation gaps |\n738\t| 4 | 2-1-workflow-yaml-json-schema | 2 | Greenfield | ~86 | Branch coverage gap, ESM require |\n739\t| 5 | 2-2-workflow-parser-module | 2 | Greenfield | 63 | Error handling catch-all, missing edge case tests |\n740\t| | **Total** | | | **~456** | 14 issues found by code review |\n741\t\n742\t### Sprint Progress\n743\t\n744\t- **Epic 1:** DONE (3/3)\n745\t- **Epic 2:** 40% (2/5) — stories 2-1 and 2-2 done\n746\t- **Epics 3-9:** Backlog\n747\t\n748\t### Day-Level Metrics\n749\t\n750\t| Metric | Value |\n751\t|--------|-------|\n752\t| Stories completed | 5 |\n753\t| Total tool calls | ~471 |\n754\t| Estimated total cost | ~$35 |\n755\t| Average cost per story | ~$7 |\n756\t| Issues found by code review | 14 |\n757\t| Issues fixed by code review | 10 |\n758\t| Issues deferred | 4 (all LOW) |\n759\t| Final test coverage | 96.63% |\n760\t| Files above 80% floor | 150/150 |\n761\t\n762\t### Recurring Issues (Unresolved After 4 Sessions)\n763\t\n764\t1. **Verification proof format failures** — caused retry loops in 3 of 4 sessions. Estimated wasted cost: $6-10 across the day.\n765\t2. **`codeharness stats` broken** — no automated cost tracking for 4 sessions.\n766\t3. **`package.