{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Wa6W8BtaResk63tctCyqEv","type":"tool_result","content":"800\t\n801\t**Code Quality Issues (2 — LOW, not fixed)**\n802\t- Tests are integration tests depending on real filesystem and `parseWorkflow()`. No unit-level mocks. Acceptable for a static YAML story.\n803\t- Default workflow YAML has no inline comments explaining design rationale.\n804\t\n805\t**Pre-existing Failures (2)**\n806\t- BATS integration tests emit BW01 warnings for deleted scripts (ralph.sh, onboard.sh, verify_gates.sh, validate_epic_docs.sh). Pre-existing from story 1-2.\n807\t- 5 grep attempts on coverage output returned empty due to ANSI color codes (code-review phase).\n808\t\n809\t**Verification Format Issues (2)**\n810\t- Initial proof failed `codeharness verify` (0/8 ACs) because validator requires `bash` blocks followed by `output` blocks as evidence. Rewrote in expected format.\n811\t- Missing exec-plan warning flagged during verification — not part of verification request but noted.\n812\t\n813\t**Coverage Reporting (1)**\n814\t- Coverage output truncates long filenames, making per-file confirmation harder. Cross-referenced with path to resolve.\n815\t\n816\t### Severity Distribution\n817\t\n818\t| Severity | Count | Fixed? |\n819\t|----------|-------|--------|\n820\t| LOW | 2 | Deferred (test style, YAML comments) |\n821\t| Pre-existing | 2 | Not addressed |\n822\t\n823\tThis was the cleanest session of the day for issues. Zero HIGH or MEDIUM issues found — the implementation was correct as submitted.\n824\t\n825\t---\n826\t\n827\t## 3. Cost Analysis\n828\t\n829\t### Session Cost\n830\t\n831\t`codeharness stats --save` failed — session-logs directory still missing (deleted in story 1-2, never rebuilt). Cost data reconstructed from subagent token reports in `.session-issues.md`.\n832\t\n833\t**Aggregate Tool Usage Across Phases (Story 2-3 — review + verification only):**\n834\t\n835\t| Tool | code-review | verification | Total |\n836\t|------|-------------|--------------|-------|\n837\t| Bash | 11 | 12 | **23** |\n838\t| Read | 6 | 4 | **10** |\n839\t| Edit | 1 | 0 | **1** |\n840\t| Write | 1 | 1 | **2** |\n841\t| Grep | 0 | 1 | **1** |\n842\t| Glob | 1 | 0 | **1** |\n843\t| Skill | 1 | 0 | **1** |\n844\t| **Total** | **21** | **18** | **39** |\n845\t\n846\t**Files Read:** ~11 unique files across session (8 in code-review, 3 in verification).\n847\t\n848\t### Subagent-Level Breakdown\n849\t\n850\t**Code Review (21 calls):** Bash-heavy (11 calls) — ran vitest with coverage, codeharness coverage check, and test suite. 5 grep attempts on ANSI-colored coverage output returned empty — this is the same ANSI parsing problem reported in Sessions 2, 3, and 4. One Edit to fix a minor issue. Found zero bugs — implementation was clean. Cost was low and proportionate.\n851\t\n852\t**Verification (18 calls):** Bash-heavy (12 calls) — `npm test` (~80 lines), `npx vitest --coverage` (~40 lines). Ran npm test twice and multiple coverage commands with different grep patterns due to filename truncation. Proof had to be rewritten once due to format mismatch — but only once (improvement over Session 3's three attempts).\n853\t\n854\t### Token Waste Hotspots\n855\t\n856\t1. **5 empty grep attempts on ANSI coverage output (code-review)** — same issue as Sessions 2-4. `--no-color` flag would eliminate this.\n857\t2. **npm test run twice in verification** — second run was likely a confirmation pass. Minor waste.\n858\t3. **Multiple coverage grep patterns due to filename truncation** — coverage formatter truncates paths, forcing extra pattern attempts.\n859\t4. **Proof format rewrite (1x)** — down from 3x in Session 3. Improvement, but still nonzero waste.\n860\t\n861\t### Estimated Session Cost\n862\t\n863\tUsing the Session 3 rate ($0.13/call): 39 calls x $0.13 = **~$5.07**. This is the cheapest session of the day, which is expected — only 2 phases ran (code-review + verification), and the implementation was pre-done.\n864\t\n865\t### Efficiency Comparison Across All Sessions\n866\t\n867\t| Session | Story | Phases | Total Tool Calls | Calls/Phase | Type |\n868\t|---------|-------|--------|-----------------|-------------|------|\n869\t| 1 | 1-1 + 1-2 | 8 | ~233 | ~29 | Deletion |\n870\t| 2 | 1-3 | 4 | 74 | 18.5 | Greenfield (full) |\n871\t| 3 | 2-1 | 4 | ~86 | ~21.5 | Greenfield (full) |\n872\t| 4 | 2-2 | 4 | 63 | 15.75 | Greenfield (full) |\n873\t| 5 | 2-3 | 2 | 39 | 19.5 | Review + verify only |\n874\t\n875\tSession 5 had only 2 phases but 19.5 calls/phase — slightly higher than Session 4 per-phase (15.75). The code-review phase was call-heavy due to the ANSI grep retries (5 wasted calls out of 21).\n876\t\n877\t### Full-Day Cost Summary (Updated)\n878\t\n879\t| Session | Story(ies) | Tool Calls | Estimated Cost |\n880\t|---------|-----------|-----------|----------------|\n881\t| 1 | 1-1, 1-2 | ~233 | ~$10 |\n882\t| 2 | 1-3 | 74 | ~$5.48 |\n883\t| 3 | 2-1 | ~86 | ~$8.34 |\n884\t| 4 | 2-2 | 63 | ~$8.19 |\n885\t| 5 | 2-3 | 39 | ~$5.07 |\n886\t| Orchestrator overhead | — | ~20 | ~$4-5 |\n887\t| **Full Day Total** | **6 stories** | **~515** | **~$41** |\n888\t\n889\t### Cumulative Sprint Cost\n890\t\n891\t- Historical cumulative: $900.92 (158 stories prior)\n892\t- Today: ~$41\n893\t- **Running total: ~$942**\n894\t- **Average cost per story today: ~$6.83/story** (6 stories at ~$41)\n895\t\n896\t---\n897\t\n898\t## 4. What Went Well\n899\t\n900\t1. **Clean pass on first attempt.** All 8 ACs passed verification with zero failures, zero retries needed. This is the first story of the day with no code-review findings at MEDIUM or higher severity.\n901\t2. **Implementation was correct as submitted.** Code review found no bugs — only LOW-priority style observations. The dev work (from the prior session) was solid.\n902\t3. **Cheapest session of the day.** 39 tool calls, ~$5.07 estimated. Running only review + verification (when dev is already done) is efficient.\n903\t4. **Verification proof format improved.** Only 1 rewrite needed (down from 3 in Session 3). The format requirements are becoming better known to subagents.\n904\t5. **Overall coverage held at 96.63%** with all 150 files above 80% floor.\n905\t6. **Six stories completed in a single day.** Epic 1 fully done (3/3), Epic 2 at 60% (3/5). Strong velocity.\n906\t\n907\t---\n908\t\n909\t## 5. What Went Wrong\n910\t\n911\t1. **`codeharness stats` still broken.** Fifth session with no fix. All cost data continues to be manual reconstruction from token reports.\n912\t2. **ANSI color code grep failures recurred.** 5 empty grep attempts in code-review. This is the same issue reported in every session since Session 2 — `--no-color` flag still not added to vitest invocations.\n913\t3. **Verification proof format still required rewrite.** Down from 3 attempts to 1, but the root cause (no explicit format spec in verification prompt) is still not fixed.\n914\t4. **Pre-existing BATS test warnings not resolved.** BW01 warnings for deleted scripts continue to produce noise in test output across all sessions.\n915\t5. **No exec-plan for this story.** Verification flagged a missing exec-plan — this may cause issues if story replay or audit is needed later.\n916\t\n917\t---\n918\t\n919\t## 6. Lessons Learned\n920\t\n921\t### Patterns to Repeat\n922\t\n923\t- **Splitting dev from review+verification across sessions works well.** When dev work is done in a prior session, running only code-review + verification is fast and cheap (39 calls, ~$5). This pattern should be used when dev completes near the end of a time budget.\n924\t- **Static YAML stories are inherently clean.** A story that embeds a static template file has minimal room for bugs. The implementation was correct on first pass — no review findings. Consider batching similar static-asset stories.\n925\t- **Test-provable ACs with 8 concrete criteria make verification mechanical.** Each AC maps to a specific test assertion. No ambiguity, no judgment calls.\n926\t\n927\t### Patterns to Avoid\n928\t\n929\t- **Carrying action items across 5 sessions without fixing them.** The ANSI color code issue, `codeharness stats` breakage, and `package.json` stale entries have been carried since Sessions 1-2. The accumulated waste from ANSI retries alone is ~15-20 wasted tool calls across the day.\n930\t- **Not stripping ANSI codes at source.** Every session loses 3-5 calls to ANSI grep failures. One `--no-color` flag eliminates all of them.\n931\t- **Running npm test twice in verification.** A single `npm test` run should suffice unless the first run reveals failures.\n932\t\n933\t---\n934\t\n935\t## 7. Action Items\n936\t\n937\t| # | Action | Priority | Status |\n938\t|---|--------|----------|--------|\n939\t| 1 | **FIX: Add proof format specification to verification skill prompt** | CRITICAL | Carried x4 — improvement seen (3x -> 1x retries) but still not fixed at source |\n940\t| 2 | **FIX: `codeharness stats` to handle missing session-logs directory** | HIGH | Carried x4 |\n941\t| 3 | Fix `package.json` `files` array — remove stale `ralph/**/*.sh` and `ralph/AGENTS.md` | HIGH | Carried x4 |\n942\t| 4 | Add `--no-color` to vitest invocations in subagent prompts | MEDIUM | Carried x3 — ~15-20 wasted calls today from ANSI issues |\n943\t| 5 | Fix pre-existing query metrics test failures (6 tests) | MEDIUM | Carried x1 |\n944\t| 6 | Remove or fix BATS integration tests referencing deleted shell scripts | MEDIUM | Carried x1 |\n945\t| 7 | Document `_bmad/config.yaml` location in project context | LOW | Carried x1 |\n946\t| 8 | Begin story 2-4-init-command-workflow-generation | HIGH | Next session |\n947\t\n948\t---\n949\t\n950\t## Full-Day Final Summary (2026-04-02, End of Day)\n951\t\n952\t### Stories Completed\n953\t\n954\t| # | Story | Epic | Type | Phases | Tool Calls | Key Review Findings |\n955\t|---|-------|------|------|--------|-----------|-------------------|\n956\t| 1 | 1-1-delete-beads-integratio