s | ~4-8 wasted glob calls |\n994\t\n995\t### Trend: Efficiency Improving\n996\t\n997\tThe day showed a clear efficiency trend for greenfield stories:\n998\t\n999\t```\n1000\tSession 2 (1-3): 18.5 calls/phase\n1001\tSession 3 (2-1): 21.5 calls/phase (schema story, more complex)\n1002\tSession 4 (2-2): 15.75 calls/phase (best full-lifecycle)\n1003\tSession 5 (2-3): 19.5 calls/phase (review-only, inflated by ANSI retries)\n1004\t```\n1005\t\n1006\tExcluding ANSI retry waste (~5 calls), Session 5 would have been ~17 calls/phase — in line with the improving trend. The subagent pattern is maturing and cost per story is stabilizing.\n1007\t\n1008\t---\n1009\t\n1010\t# Session Retrospective — 2026-04-02 (Session 6: Stories 2-3 + 2-4 Final Rollup)\n1011\t\n1012\t**Generated:** 2026-04-02T18:45 UTC\n1013\t\n1014\t## 1. Session Summary\n1015\t\n1016\t**Date:** 2026-04-02\n1017\t**Stories attempted this session:** 2\n1018\t**Stories completed this session:** 2\n1019\t**Full-day stories completed:** 7 (1-1, 1-2, 1-3, 2-1, 2-2, 2-3, 2-4)\n1020\t\n1021\t| Story | Phases Run | Outcome | Commit |\n1022\t|-------|-----------|---------|--------|\n1023\t| 2-3-default-embedded-workflow | create-story, code-review, verification | done | `5070259` |\n1024\t| 2-4-init-command-workflow-generation | create-story, dev-story, code-review, verification | done | `5a17066` |\n1025\t\n1026\tThis session completed the remaining two stories from the day's autonomous run. Story 2-3 embeds the default workflow YAML template. Story 2-4 adds workflow generation to the `codeharness init` command — when a user runs `init`, it now copies the default workflow to `.codeharness/workflows/default.yaml`. Epic 2 is now 80% complete (4/5) with only story 2-5 (validate command) remaining.\n1027\t\n1028\t**Sprint progress after session:** Epic 1 done (3/3). Epic 2 at 80% (4/5). 7/28 total stories done (25%).\n1029\t\n1030\t---\n1031\t\n1032\t## 2. Issues Analysis\n1033\t\n1034\t### Categorized Issues from Session Log\n1035\t\n1036\t**Bugs Found by Code Review (3 — all fixed)**\n1037\t- **MEDIUM:** `handleRerun()` ignored `--force` flag for workflow generation — re-run with `--force` did not regenerate the workflow file.\n1038\t- **MEDIUM:** `handleRerun()` left `result.workflow` undefined when workflow file was missing — downstream consumers would get undefined instead of a clear state.\n1039\t- **MEDIUM:** No test coverage for re-run+force code path — 3 tests added to cover the gap.\n1040\t\n1041\t**Code Quality Issues (2 — LOW, not fixed)**\n1042\t- Template source file missing produces generic error instead of descriptive \"template not found\" message.\n1043\t- `.codeharness/workflows/default.yaml` path hardcoded in 7+ locations — should be a constant.\n1044\t\n1045\t**Spec/Config Gaps (4)**\n1046\t- `workflow.md` vs `workflow.yaml` extension mismatch in skill trigger configuration.\n1047\t- `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` referenced in workflow.yaml but actual path is `_bmad/config.yaml` — fifth time this session the path was wrong.\n1048\t- No `project-context.md` exists in this project.\n1049\t- Story key `2-4-init-command-workflow-generation` not found verbatim in epics file (uses \"Story 2.4\" format).\n1050\t\n1051\t**Verification Format Issues (2)**\n1052\t- Story 2-3: Initial proof failed (0/8 ACs) — validator requires `bash` blocks followed by `output` blocks. Rewrote in expected format.\n1053\t- Story 2-4: Same format issue — first proof didn't match parser's expected `## AC N:` top-level format. Rewrote.\n1054\t\n1055\t**Pre-existing Failures (2)**\n1056\t- BATS integration tests (onboard, ralph, verify_gates, validate_epic_docs) fail with code 127 — shell scripts deleted in story 1-2.\n1057\t- 48 lint warnings — all pre-existing unused-var/regex issues in other modules.\n1058\t\n1059\t### Severity Distribution\n1060\t\n1061\t| Severity | Count | Fixed? |\n1062\t|----------|-------|--------|\n1063\t| MEDIUM | 3 | All 3 fixed (code review) |\n1064\t| LOW | 2 | Deferred |\n1065\t| Pre-existing | 2 | Not addressed |\n1066\t\n1067\t---\n1068\t\n1069\t## 3. Cost Analysis\n1070\t\n1071\t### Session Cost\n1072\t\n1073\t`codeharness stats --save` failed — session-logs directory still missing. Cost reconstructed from subagent token reports.\n1074\t\n1075\t**Story 2-3 (create-story + code-review + verification):**\n1076\t\n1077\t| Tool | create-story | code-review | verification | Total |\n1078\t|------|-------------|-------------|--------------|-------|\n1079\t| Bash | 2 | 11 | 12 | **25** |\n1080\t| Read | 11 | 6 | 4 | **21** |\n1081\t| Edit | 0 | 1 | 0 | **1** |\n1082\t| Write | 1 | 1 | 1 | **3** |\n1083\t| Grep | 2 | 0 | 1 | **3** |\n1084\t| Glob | 5 | 1 | 0 | **6** |\n1085\t| Skill | 1 | 1 | 0 | **2** |\n1086\t| **Total** | **18** | **21** | **18** | **57** |\n1087\t\n1088\t**Story 2-4 (create-story + dev-story + code-review + verification):**\n1089\t\n1090\t| Tool | create-story | dev-story | code-review | verification | Total |\n1091\t|------|-------------|-----------|-------------|--------------|-------|\n1092\t| Bash | 5 | 4 | 7 | 10 | **26** |\n1093\t| Read | 10 | 8 | 8 | 2 | **28** |\n1094\t| Edit | 0 | 10 | 3 | 0 | **13** |\n1095\t| Write | 1 | 0 | 0 | 1 | **2** |\n1096\t| Grep | 7 | 0 | 0 | 5 | **12** |\n1097\t| Glob | 8 | 1 | 1 | 0 | **10** |\n1098\t| Skill | 1 | 1 | 1 | 0 | **3** |\n1099\t| **Total** | **24** | **18** | **18** | **16** | **76** |\n1100\t\n1101\t**Session Total: 133 tool calls (57 for 2-3, 76 for 2-4)**\n1102\t\n1103\t### Subagent-Level Breakdown\n1104\t\n1105\t**Story 2-3 create-story (18 calls):** Read-heavy (11 calls). All artifacts located and readable. No problems, no redundancy.\n1106\t\n1107\t**Story 2-3 code-review (21 calls):** Bash-heavy (11 calls). Found no bugs — implementation was correct. 5 grep attempts on ANSI coverage output returned empty (same recurring issue). One Edit for a minor fix. Clean pass.\n1108\t\n1109\t**Story 2-3 verification (18 calls):** Ran npm test twice, multiple coverage commands with different grep patterns due to filename truncation. Proof format required one rewrite.\n1110\t\n1111\t**Story 2-4 create-story (24 calls):** Most tool-intensive create-story of the day. 8 Glob attempts and 7 Grep calls to locate files — the `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` path confusion and story key format mismatch added 3 wasted Glob attempts.\n1112\t\n1113\t**Story 2-4 dev-story (18 calls):** Edit-heavy (10 edits). Clean implementation — 30/30 tests pass, build succeeds. No redundancy.\n1114\t\n1115\t**Story 2-4 code-review (18 calls):** Found and fixed 3 MEDIUM bugs. Efficient — no wasted calls. All findings were legitimate.\n1116\t\n1117\t**Story 2-4 verification (16 calls):** Leanest verification of the day. Proof format required one rewrite but otherwise efficient. AC 4 (--force flag) verified via source code grep rather than --help invocation — weaker but acceptable for test-provable tier.\n1118\t\n1119\t### Token Waste Hotspots\n1120\t\n1121\t1. **5 ANSI grep failures in 2-3 code-review** — same issue, 6th session.\n1122\t2. **3 Glob attempts in 2-4 create-story** to find workflow directory structure — path confusion.\n1123\t3. **npm test run twice in 2-3 verification** — confirmation run was unnecessary.\n1124\t4. **Coverage commands with multiple grep patterns in 2-3 verification** — truncated filenames.\n1125\t5. **Proof format rewrite in both stories** — 2 rewrites total, down from 3+1 in Sessions 3-5.\n1126\t\n1127\t### Estimated Session Cost\n1128\t\n1129\tUsing $0.13/call rate: 133 calls x $0.13 = **~$17.29**\n1130\t\n1131\t### Full-Day Cost Summary (Final)\n1132\t\n1133\t| Session | Story(ies) | Tool Calls | Estimated Cost |\n1134\t|---------|-----------|-----------|----------------|\n1135\t| 1 | 1-1, 1-2 | ~233 | ~$10 |\n1136\t| 2 | 1-3 | 74 | ~$5.48 |\n1137\t| 3 | 2-1 | ~86 | ~$8.34 |\n1138\t| 4 | 2-2 | 63 | ~$8.19 |\n1139\t| 5 | 2-3 (review+verify) | 39 | ~$5.07 |\n1140\t| 6 | 2-3 (create) + 2-4 (full) | 133 | ~$17.29 |\n1141\t| Orchestrator overhead | — | ~25 | ~$5 |\n1142\t| **Full Day Total** | **7 stories** | **~653** | **~$59** |\n1143\t\n1144\t### Cumulative Sprint Cost\n1145\t\n1146\t- Historical cumulative: $900.92 (158 stories prior)\n1147\t- Today: ~$59\n1148\t- **Running total: ~$960**\n1149\t- **Average cost per story today: ~$8.43/story** (7 stories at ~$59)\n1150\t\n1151\tThe per-story cost is higher than the historical average ($4.17) due to Opus 4 pricing and larger context windows from accumulated v2 architecture artifacts.\n1152\t\n1153\t---\n1154\t\n1155\t## 4. What Went Well\n1156\t\n1157\t1. **Seven stories completed in a single day.** Epic 1 fully done (3/3), Epic 2 at 80% (4/5). This is the highest single-day story throughput recorded.\n1158\t2. **All stories passed on first attempt.** Zero story failures, zero retries at the story level. Every story was completed in a single pass through the pipeline.\n1159\t3. **Code review caught 3 real bugs in story 2-4.** The `handleRerun()` --force flag bug and undefined `result.workflow` would have been user-facing issues. Code review continues to justify its cost.\n1160\t4. **Story 2-4 verification was the leanest of the day (16 calls).** The verification skill is improving — fewer retries, more focused evidence gathering.\n1161\t5. **Overall test coverage held at 96.64%** with all files above 80% floor. Coverage stayed stable across all 7 stories.\n1162\t6. **Story 2-3 was the cleanest implementation.** Zero bugs found in code review. Static asset stories are inherently low-risk.\n1163\t7. **Sprint is 25% complete (7/28 stories).** At this velocity (~7 stories/day), the full sprint could be completed in ~3 more days.\n1164\t\n1165\t---\n1166\t\n1167\t## 5. What Went Wrong\n1168\t\n1169\t1. **`codeharness stats` still broken.** Sixth session. No automated cost tracking. All cost data is manual reconstruction from token reports — this takes ~5 minutes per session and is error-prone.\n1170\t2. **Verification proof format still required rewrites.** Both stories needed proof rewrites. Five of 6 sessions today hit this issue. The action item to fix the verification prompt has been carried since Session 1 and has never been implemented.\n1171\t3. **ANSI color code grep failures continue.** 5 wasted calls in this session alone. Estimated ~20-25 wasted calls across the full day. The `--no-color` fix has been carried since Session 2.\n1172\t4. **`_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` path confusion — fifth occurrence.** Create-story agents keep looking for `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` but the actual path is `_bmad/config.yaml`. This wastes 2-3 Glob calls per occurrence.\n1173\t5. **48 pre-existing lint warnings ignored.** These are noise in every lint run. None are related to today's work but they obscure real issues.\n1174\t6. **BATS integration tests still failing.** Shell scripts deleted in story 1-2 but BATS tests still reference them. Code 127 errors in every test run.\n1175\t\n1176\t---\n1177\t\n1178\t## 6. Lessons Learned\n1179\t\n1180\t### Patterns to Repeat\n1181\t\n1182\t- **7 stories/day is achievable with greenfield work.** The pipeline (create-story -> dev-story -> code-review -> verification) handles greenfield modules efficiently. Deletion stories are slower (~29 calls/phase vs ~17 calls/phase for greenfield).\n1183\t- **Code review as a separate phase remains essential.** 3 MEDIUM bugs caught in story 2-4 that dev phase missed. The --force flag bug would have been a user-reported issue.\n1184\t- **Static asset stories are fast and clean.** Story 2-3 (embed default workflow) had zero review findings. Consider batching similar template/asset stories.\n1185\t- **Splitting dev and review across sessions works.** Story 2-3 dev was done in a prior session; review+verification in this session. This pattern is efficient when time budgets are tight.\n1186\t\n1187\t### Patterns to Avoid\n1188\t\n1189\t- **Carrying action items indefinitely.** Five action items have been carried across 4-6 sessions without being fixed. The cumulative waste from ANSI retries alone is ~20-25 tool calls today (~$3). Fix recurring issues between sprints, not during sprints.\n1190\t- **Hardcoding paths in 7+ locations.** Story 2-4 has `.codeharness/workflows/default.yaml` hardcoded in 7+ places. This should be a constant. The code review noted it but deferred as LOW.\n1191\t- **Not running `codeharness stats --save` before deleting session-logs.** This was the root cause of all cost tracking issues today. The lesson was identified in Session 1 but never applied retroactively.\n1192\t\n1193\t---\n1194\t\n1195\t## 7. Action Items\n1196\t\n1197\t| # | Action | Priority | Status |\n1198\t|---|--------|----------|--------|\n1199\t| 1 | **FIX: Add proof format specification to verification skill prompt** — `## AC N: Title` headers + `bash`/`output` evidence blocks | CRITICAL | Carried x5 — still causing rewrites in 5/6 sessions |\n1200\t| 2 | **FIX: Add `--no-color` to vitest invocations in subagent prompts** | HIGH | Carried x4 — ~25 wasted calls today |\n1201\t| 3 | **FIX: `codeharness stats` to handle missing session-logs directory** | HIGH | Carried x5 |\n1202\t| 4 | Fix `package.json` `files` array — remove stale `ralph/**/*.sh` and `ralph/AGENTS.md` | HIGH | Carried x5 |\n1203\t| 5 | Fix pre-existing query metrics test failures (6 tests) | MEDIUM | Carried x2 |\n1204\t| 6 | Remove or fix BATS integration tests referencing deleted shell scripts | MEDIUM | Carried x2 |\n1205\t| 7 | Extract `.codeharness/workflows/default.yaml` path as a constant | LOW | New |\n1206\t| 8 | Document `_bmad/config.yaml` actual location (not `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml`) | LOW | Carried x2 |\n1207\t| 9 | Begin story 2-5-validate-command to complete Epic 2 | HIGH | Next session |\n1208\t\n1209\t---\n1210\t\n1211\t## Full-Day Final Summary (2026-04-02, Session 6 — True End of Day)\n1212\t\n1213\t### Stories Completed\n1214\t\n1215\t| # | Story | Epic | Type | Phases | Tool Calls | Key Review Findings |\n1216\t|---|-------|------|------|--------|-----------|-------------------|\n1217\t| 1 | 1-1-delete-beads-integration | 1 | Deletion | 4 | ~119 | Dead type members, stale JSDoc |\n1218\t| 2 | 1-2-delete-ralph-loop-legacy-verification | 1 | Deletion | 4 | ~114 | Incomplete ralph/ deletion, broken stats.ts |\n1219\t| 3 | 1-3-workflow-state-module | 1 | Greenfield | 4 | 74 | Naming collision, validation gaps |\n1220\t| 4 | 2-1-workflow-yaml-json-schema | 2 | Greenfield | 4 | ~86 | Branch coverage gap, ESM require |\n1221\t| 5 | 2-2-workflow-parser-module | 2 | Greenfield | 4 | 63 | Error handling catch-all, missing edge cases |\n1222\t| 6 | 2-3-default-embedded-workflow | 2 | Static asset | 3+2 | ~96 | None (clean pass) |\n1223\t| 7 | 2-4-init-command-workflow-generation | 2 | Greenfield | 4 | 76 | --force flag bug, undefined result.workflow, missing test coverage |\n1224\t|   | **Total** | | | **29** | **~653** | 17 issues found by code review |\n1225\t\n1226\t### Sprint Progress\n1227\t\n1228\t- **Epic 1:** DONE (3/3)\n1229\t- **Epic 2:** 80% (4/5) — stories 2-1 through 2-4 done; 2-5 in backlog\n1230\t- **Epics 3-9:** Backlog\n1231\t- **Overall:** 7/28 stories done (25%)\n1232\t\n1233\t### Day-Level Metrics\n1234\t\n1235\t| Metric | Value |\n1236\t|--------|-------|\n1237\t| Stories completed | 7 |\n1238\t| Total tool calls | ~653 |\n1239\t| Estimated total cost | ~$59 |\n1240\t| Average cost per story | ~$8.43 |\n1241\t| Issues found by code review | 17 |\n1242\t| Issues fixed by code review | 13 |\n1243\t| Issues deferred | 4 (all LOW) |\n1244\t| Final test coverage | 96.64% |\n1245\t| Files above 80% floor | 150/150 |\n1246\t| Story failure rate | 0% (7/7 first-attempt success) |\n1247\t| Verification proof format failures | 5/7 stories needed rewrite |\n1248\t\n1249\t### Recurring Issues (Unresolved After 6 Sessions)\n1250\t\n1251\t| Issue | Sessions Carried | Estimated Waste Today | Fix Effort |\n1252\t|-------|-----------------|----------------------|------------|\n1253\t| Verification proof format failures | 5 of 6 sessions | ~$6-10 | Low (prompt update) |\n1254\t| ANSI color code grep failures | 5 of 6 sessions | ~$3 (25 calls) | Low (one flag) |\n1255\t| `codeharness stats` broken | 6 sessions | Manual work every session | Medium |\n1256\t| `package.json` stale entries | 5 sessions | Tech debt | Low |\n1257\t| `_bmad/config.yaml` path confusion | 5 sessions | ~$1 (8-10 calls) | Low |\n1258\t\n1259\t**Total estimated waste from unfixed recurring issues: ~$10-14 today (17-24% of total spend).**\n1260\t\n1261\t### Efficiency Trend (Greenfield Stories)\n1262\t\n1263\t```\n1264\tSession 2 (1-3): 18.5 calls/phase\n1265\tSession 3 (2-1): 21.5 calls/phase\n1266\tSession 4 (2-2): 15.75 calls/phase (best full-lifecycle)\n1267\tSession 6 (2-4): 19.0 calls/phase\n1268\t```\n1269\t\n1270\tEfficiency is stabilizing around 17-20 calls/phase for greenfield stories. The outlier is Session 3 (2-1) which was the first schema story and involved more exploration. The pipeline has matured to a predictable cost profile.\n1271\t\n1272\t### Velocity Projection\n1273\t\n1274\tAt 7 stories/day, the remaining 21 stories could be completed in ~3 days. However, later epics (agent dispatch, flow execution, evaluator, circuit breaker) are more complex than Epic 1-2 foundation stories. Realistic projection: **5-7 more days to complete the sprint**, assuming similar daily time budgets and no major blockers.\n1275\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_018KGgogVCKrkpaQRviEJXhG","session_id":"5fca15c0-771e-463c-9e4f-c528b230e359","uuid":"8b1b6fa1-fb50-4f9d-b3b5-7a775110a61b","timestamp":"2026-04-02T15:07:54.793Z"}
